## 🏥 Health Assessment
• **Healthiness Score:** 7/10 

• **Pros:**
    - **Good source of carbohydrates:** The dosa and idli are good sources of carbohydrates, which provide energy.
    - **Rich in protein:** The sambar contains lentils, which are a good source of protein.
    - **Fiber-rich:** The dosa and idli are made with fermented rice and lentils, which are good sources of fiber.
    - **Healthy Fats:** Coconut chutney provides some healthy fats.

• **Cons:**
    - **High in sodium:** The sambar can be high in sodium due to the use of salt. 
    - **May be heavy to digest:** This meal can be heavy to digest for some people, especially if eaten in large quantities.

## 💡 Recommendations
• **Healthier Alternatives:**
    - **Use less salt in the sambar.**
    - **Replace the coconut chutney with a vegetable chutney.**

• **Portion Size Suggestions:**
    - **One dosa and two idlis** are a good portion size for a healthy meal.

• **Best Time to Consume:** 
    - This meal is best consumed for **breakfast or lunch**.
